article.headline: Colgate 55, Dartmouth 43
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Kendall Chones scored 14 points to lead Colgate to a 55-43 victory over winless Dartmouth on Saturday. The Big Green (0-3) shot just 30.8 percent for the game but mounted a comeback in the second half, twice pulling within five points before falling short. The Raiders (1-1) took a 25-20 lead into the locker room after leading by as much as 11 in the first half. Baskets by Alex Barnett and Michael Giovacchini brought Dartmouth within five points late in the game. Barnett led Dartmouth with 12 points on 6-of-17 shooting from the field. Kyle Chones led Colgate with eight rebounds.
